cturing impacts competitive position directly, as indicated by the resource-based view of manufacturing strategy. This exploratory study provides new empirical evidence that the M/M interface harmony, as expressed by the functions' ability to work together, matters significantly to business outcomes directly and indirectly. (C) 2002 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.
